name: The Witch
description:
When the hour is nigh, and hopelessness is sinking in, and the wolves all cry to fill the night with hollering, when your eyes are red, and emptiness is all you know with the darkness fed - I will be your scarecrow. 'Cause I'm bleeding out, so if the last thing that I do is bring you down - I'll bleed out for you. So I bare my skin and I count my sins, and I close my eyes, and I take it in, and I'm bleeding out, I'm bleeding out for you, for you...

Oil on canvas.
